  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Caravan of Hope for IDPs in Maguindanao and North Cotabato</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Conflict-affected Families</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this response, LWR will serve over 2,600 families (roughly 13,000 people) in Mamasapano municipality, as assessments indicate that area has the greatest needs from the impact of the conflict. They are currently working in 8 evacuation centers.LWR&#x2019;s response seeks to meet the emergency needs of the conflict-affected and displaced population in Mindanao through the provision and distribution of essential emergency relief to IDPs. Specific activities are outlined below: 
Non Food Items (NFIs):
-NFIs including solar lamps, household kits and school kits to help meet basic needs while displaced.
Water, Sanitation and Hygiene (WSH):
-Hygiene kits and personal care kits to ensure dignity of populations

-Jerry cans for water storage
-Water filtration units</narrative>
  </description>
